recipes.name: Carrot Cake
recipes.instructions:
If you have a couple of bowls and can stir ingredients together, you can make this easy cake! You’ll start by whisking the dry ingredients in one bowl, and do the same with the wet ingredients in another.

Making this cake batter reminds me of making pancakes or muffins. All you need to do is fold the dry ingredients into the wet, add your carrots, nuts, and raisins, and you are done. It’s that easy!

recipes.name: Gammon
ingredients: 5 pounds (2.5 kilogram) cooked bone-in ham (shank or butt portion)
1/4 cup (60 milliliters) packed brown sugar or honey
recipes.instructions:
Preheat oven to 325°F (160°C). Score ham and stud with cloves. Place ham on rack in roasting pan.
2	Bake 1-1/2 to 2-1/4 hours or until internal temperature reaches 140°F (60°C).
3	Combine mustard, Worcestershire and sugar in small saucepan. Heat just to a boil, stirring until sugar melts.
4	Baste ham with glaze frequently during last 30 minutes of baking. Serve additional glaze or honey mustard on the side.
5	For Marmalade Glazed Ham: Combine 3/4 cup (175 mL) orange marmalade, 1/3 cup (75 mL) FRENCH'S® Honey Mustard and 2 tablespoons (30 mL) orange juice in saucepan. Stir and heat until melted and smooth.

recipes.name: Grilled Hot Dogs
ingredients:
1 bottle (341ml) lager beer
1/2 cup (125 milliliters) French’s Classic Yellow Mustard

plus more for topping
2 tablespoons (30 milliliters) Liquid Honey Bear
2 tablespoons (30 milliliters) butter
recipes.instructions:
Mix beer, Mustard and honey in medium bowl; set aside.
2	Heat large cast iron skillet on grill over medium heat 3 minutes. Melt butter in skillet. Add onions; cook 2 to 3 minutes or until softened and lightly browned. Add hot dogs to skillet and stir in beer mixture. Cook 10 minutes; stirring occasionally.
3	Remove hot dogs from skillet and place directly on grill; cook 2 to 3 minutes, basting with sauce from skillet. Meanwhile, toast rolls on grill, open-side down, about 30 seconds.
4	To serve, place hot dogs on rolls. Top with onions and drizzle with additional Mustard and desired condiments, if desired.
